1
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:55,220
Hey, listen. I know I'm not the usual big shot

2
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:59,350
you're used to dealing with,
but a deal this small?

3
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:05,000
I can manage on my own.

4
00:01:05,060 --> 00:01:08,430
I've got connection in In-sa-dong.

5
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:09,900
In-sa-dong is great.

6
00:01:11,870 --> 00:01:14,800
Since it's my first time,

7
00:01:14,870 --> 00:01:17,000
I wasn't sure what to do.

8
00:01:18,070 --> 00:01:21,310
But I'll make sure to give you a fat commission.

9
00:01:22,310 --> 00:01:24,870
Thank you for that.
Let's see the goods.

10
00:01:24,950 --> 00:01:26,280
Sure, sure.

11
00:01:26,950 --> 00:01:28,180
Ahh, now,

12
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:32,480
this is called the Blue Dragon Tea Cup

13
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:35,490
used by the Ming Dynasty nobles.

14
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:42,090
I hear it goes at 300 million Yen in Japan.

15
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:43,760
- How much?
- 300 million Yen

16
00:01:44,870 --> 00:01:47,100
I own this tiny shop,

17
00:01:47,170 --> 00:01:50,300
so I go to China to get merchandise.

18
00:01:50,370 --> 00:01:54,710
Last trip to Guangzhou,
I bought this off an old Chinese man.

19
00:01:54,780 --> 00:01:58,270
Then as soon as I get back to Korea,

20
00:01:58,350 --> 00:02:00,680
that old man gets arrested by PSB

21
00:02:00,750 --> 00:02:02,580
- For smuggling cultural properties
- Oh yeah?

22
00:02:02,650 --> 00:02:04,210
This old man,

23
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:07,590
he'd run errands for Japanese scholars during the war

24
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:09,090
and stashed away a few artifacts.

25
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:13,990
Not knowing its worth,
he gave it to me for nothing.

26
00:02:14,060 --> 00:02:18,400
Wow, you lucked out.

27
00:02:20,070 --> 00:02:23,100
The timing was impeccable.

28
00:02:23,170 --> 00:02:24,940
At first he didn't want to sell.

29
00:02:25,010 --> 00:02:25,800
Why?

30
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,610
Some Korean dude

31
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:31,670
begged the old man to sell the goods to him.

32
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:35,080
I was like, 'This is it!'
'This is the stuff.'

33
00:02:35,150 --> 00:02:36,480
So I called higher.

34
00:02:36,550 --> 00:02:37,990
- How much?
- 5 grand

35
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:39,880
- How much?
- 5 grand

36
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:44,780
Haha, you lucky bastard.

37
00:02:46,260 --> 00:02:47,790
High-five!

38
00:02:47,860 --> 00:02:51,090
Whoever he was,
what a poor schmuck.

39
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:52,100
Let me shake your hand, man.

40
00:02:54,170 --> 00:02:55,400
That's me.

41
00:02:55,470 --> 00:02:55,990
What?

42
00:02:58,770 --> 00:03:02,110
That poor schmuck.
That was me, you jerk.

43
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:03,970
Wait, wait...

44
00:03:04,050 --> 00:03:07,980
It took me over 2 months to locate the stuff.

45
00:03:08,050 --> 00:03:11,080
Then you showed up,
and I missed it by two hours?

46
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:18,290
What's this?

47
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,590
Blue Dragon Tea Cup

48
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:23,390
Don't you think I know that?
Where is it?

49
00:03:23,970 --> 00:03:24,990
- At home
- Where?

50
00:03:25,070 --> 00:03:26,800
At home,
at home, home...

51
00:03:26,870 --> 00:03:28,500
I hid it at home.

52
00:03:28,570 --> 00:03:31,400
No one knows.
Not even my wife.

53
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,900
Mr. Chang-In Ghang!

54
00:03:35,180 --> 00:03:36,580
It's the police.

55
00:03:36,650 --> 00:03:38,370
Did you call the cops, huh?

56
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,950
- Are you Chang-in Ghang?
- Yes

57
00:03:49,030 --> 00:03:50,120
Chang-In Ghang,
you're under arrest

58
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:51,630
for violation of cultural protection act.

59
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:52,520
Where's your warrant?

60
00:04:02,810 --> 00:04:06,570
Show me the warrant.
Where are you taking me? It hurts!

61
00:04:30,770 --> 00:04:31,700
Call it in.

62
00:04:33,370 --> 00:04:35,000
Let's go.

63
00:05:02,170 --> 00:05:03,500
Check the roof, go!

64
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:06,800
Man down.
Man down.

65
00:05:06,870 --> 00:05:08,840
Male, mid-30s.
John Doe.

66
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:11,600
Fell from the roof top during the arrest.

67
00:05:37,770 --> 00:05:41,400
Villain and Widow

68
00:05:48,580 --> 00:05:51,780
You're in 80 km/h zone.

69
00:05:51,850 --> 00:05:54,280
Please slow down.

70
00:05:55,050 --> 00:05:56,780
Turn it down!

71
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:10,490
Alarm disabled.
Welcome.

72
00:06:16,670 --> 00:06:18,300
I'm never going to see the grandparents again,

73
00:06:18,370 --> 00:06:19,810
not even for the holidays.

74
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:22,070
I don't know why we keep going.
Dad's not around anymore.

75
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:23,270
That's enough.

76
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:40,590
You have to weed the yard after it rains...

77
00:06:45,870 --> 00:06:49,400
Your home is now secured.

78
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:54,510
Your yard's full of weed.

79
00:06:56,150 --> 00:06:56,670
What?

80
00:06:56,750 --> 00:07:00,270
You need to weed it out to grow something.

81
00:07:00,350 --> 00:07:02,080
We don't grow anything anymore.

82
00:07:02,150 --> 00:07:04,880
We buy everything from the store
with pesticide all over them.

83
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:10,280
Why do I even bother...

84
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:28,930
Room Available to Rent

85
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:42,180
So, Mr. Ghang's never seen the goods in person...

86
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:46,160
The Chinese who sold the stuff
got caught by PSB for smuggling.

87
00:07:46,230 --> 00:07:48,290
It was just bad timing.

88
00:07:49,170 --> 00:07:52,100
Didn't you guys look into it?

89
00:07:52,170 --> 00:07:53,690
Yeah, we figured out what's going on.

90
00:07:53,770 --> 00:07:55,100
Well, then.

91
00:07:55,170 --> 00:07:57,700
We just bring you the goods,
get it appraised,

92
00:07:58,170 --> 00:07:59,510
And if it is good,
you pay us.

93
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,680
If it isn't, you don't.
What's the big deal?

94
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:06,510
I believe my boss is entitled to an explanation.

95
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:07,780
Entitled?

96
00:08:10,050 --> 00:08:14,180
Not that I doubt your abilities,
Mr. Ghang

97
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:19,090
I just want to make sure if you need any help,

98
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,890
say, more people

99
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,900
No, I don't need more people.

100
00:08:22,970 --> 00:08:27,630
Well, if there aren't any questions,
we'll see ourselves out.

101
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:41,180
He's paying us 2 million dollars.
Was it so hard to be nice?

102
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:43,380
Is he really the president of this company?

103
00:08:43,450 --> 00:08:44,380
What do you mean?

104
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:47,380
Why is he handling things directly?

105
00:08:47,460 --> 00:08:48,980
Is that a problem?

106
00:08:49,060 --> 00:08:51,690
He needs to delegate to his people.

107
00:08:52,260 --> 00:08:54,590
He's too exposed from the start.

108
00:08:59,570 --> 00:09:01,700
He's just really desperate.

109
00:09:01,770 --> 00:09:04,600
He's got a gallery at the headquarters.

110
00:09:05,110 --> 00:09:07,510
He took 10 million from arts
budget behind his father's back

111
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:09,770
for money laundering and lost
everything in bad investment.

112
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:12,680
So he needs something to make up for it,
right away.

113
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:14,580
Pardon me.

114
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,280
My name is Mr. Song.

115
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:20,380
If you need anything,
please call me any time.

116
00:09:31,870 --> 00:09:33,390
Who's the midget?

117
00:09:33,970 --> 00:09:35,600
Some punk.

118
00:09:35,670 --> 00:09:38,200
Mr. Ha takes him around as his bodyguard.

119
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:41,510
Show off at the clubs,
you know.

120
00:09:43,050 --> 00:09:44,880
Real mature.

121
00:09:46,050 --> 00:09:48,980
Don't underestimate residential security system.

122
00:09:49,450 --> 00:09:51,890
You can go in and out of a jewelry shop in a minute,

123
00:09:51,950 --> 00:09:54,290
but this takes at least 3 to 4 days.

124
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:57,590
You look into the security company.

125
00:09:58,290 --> 00:10:00,690
Who's got time to research all that?

126
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:02,890
Delaying will upset Mr. Ha.

127
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:06,490
Why should I care,
he hasn't paid me up front.

128
00:10:06,570 --> 00:10:10,200
Can't you just tie them up and go through the house?

129
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:11,500
It's only a woman and her daughter.

130
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:15,580
Sure, because when I untie them,

131
00:10:15,650 --> 00:10:20,450
she'll say 'Thank you'.
Just like that. Sure.

132
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:23,280
Just make sure they won't want to call the cops.

133
00:10:23,350 --> 00:10:24,580
How do I do that?

134
00:10:24,650 --> 00:10:28,090
- You know how.
- Seriously, how?

135
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:30,790
You know... just...

136
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:32,190
Must I say it out loud?

137
00:10:32,260 --> 00:10:34,090
What if it goes bad?

138
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:36,600
I'd have to rot in jail for another 5~6 years.

139
00:10:37,370 --> 00:10:41,500
Chang-In, life is all about preparing for the future.

140
00:10:41,570 --> 00:10:43,500
That requires money.

141
00:10:44,370 --> 00:10:46,100
This is my last chance.

142
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:48,300
I'm old.

143
00:10:48,950 --> 00:10:51,970
This guy is paying us 2 million at once.
In cash!

144
00:10:52,050 --> 00:10:53,280
Opportunities like this don't come again.

145
00:10:54,850 --> 00:10:58,180
This is literally, 'show me the money'.
'Show me the money!'

146
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:10,890
How about just 3 grand?

147
00:11:15,870 --> 00:11:18,400
It must be hard for you, too.

148
00:11:25,050 --> 00:11:28,880
Anyone interested in renting my spare room upstairs?

149
00:11:28,950 --> 00:11:30,680
That's not an easy sale.

150
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:33,480
It's just a room,
in someone's home.

151
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:37,580
Don't young people look for studios?

152
00:11:37,660 --> 00:11:40,690
Why would kids want to live in your neighborhood?

153
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:41,990
They want to live in the city.

154
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:59,280
Mom, I want to get my eyes done.

155
00:12:03,450 --> 00:12:07,480
Mom, please?
Can I?

156
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,390
Please?

157
00:12:09,460 --> 00:12:11,390
Your eyes are just fine.

158
00:12:12,460 --> 00:12:14,190
You're not ugly.

159
00:12:14,260 --> 00:12:15,990
I am ugly.

160
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:17,790
No wonder I can't get any parts.

161
00:12:17,870 --> 00:12:21,200
You didn't fail your auditions because you're ugly.

162
00:12:21,270 --> 00:12:23,700
It's because you can't act.

163
00:12:23,770 --> 00:12:25,710
I want cosmetic surgery!

164
00:12:25,780 --> 00:12:26,900
I have no money.

165
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:29,170
You always say that.
Come on, mom.

166
00:12:29,250 --> 00:12:31,680
Please?
Just once?!

167
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:32,770
- I got no money. None.
- Surgery!

168
00:12:32,850 --> 00:12:35,780
No money. No money.
Your mom never has any.

169
00:13:30,170 --> 00:13:31,900
Who is it?

170
00:13:31,970 --> 00:13:33,810
I'm here to check out your room.

171
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:39,270
This room is really perfect for just one person.

172
00:13:42,590 --> 00:13:45,990
I don't mean to be rude,
but what kind of work do you do?

173
00:13:48,190 --> 00:13:50,490
What do I look like I do?

174
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:56,790
Since you came all the way out here for a room,

175
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:01,800
You probably need a quiet work space

176
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:07,600
You're right.
I'm a writer.

177
00:14:09,450 --> 00:14:11,780
I see,
what kind of writer?

178
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:15,680
I write trashy comments on the Internet.

179
00:14:16,950 --> 00:14:17,680
Excuse me?

180
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:21,080
I'm kidding.

181
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,880
I write novels.

182
00:14:24,460 --> 00:14:28,900
Oh, you're an author.

183
00:14:28,970 --> 00:14:30,990
No, not a big author.

184
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:33,690
I'm a bit peculiar.

185
00:14:33,770 --> 00:14:37,000
I just can't write in hotel rooms,

186
00:14:37,070 --> 00:14:38,900
and the city is too loud.

187
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,500
This neighborhood is really quiet.

188
00:14:41,580 --> 00:14:42,370
Oh yeah?

189
00:14:42,950 --> 00:14:46,380
Well, the room seems just fine.

190
00:14:46,950 --> 00:14:49,470
Could I trouble you for a cup of tea?

191
00:15:01,260 --> 00:15:06,200
How long does it take to write?

192
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:09,900
Well, it depends on the book.

193
00:15:10,570 --> 00:15:14,410
This one,
I think maybe about a month.

194
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:16,570
So you're looking for short-term lease.

195
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:18,080
Yes, I am.

196
00:15:24,450 --> 00:15:27,080
Wow, you have a nice view.

197
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:29,090
Hmm?
Yeah.

198
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:31,590
How are the neighbors?

199
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:33,560
Do they visit each other often?

200
00:15:33,630 --> 00:15:34,620
No, not really.

201
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:37,390
They're mostly old folks being concerned.

202
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:37,990
Here's your tea.

203
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:39,590
Thank you.

204
00:15:45,070 --> 00:15:47,600
Hmm, this tea is Tie Guan Yin.

205
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:50,940
You must know a lot about tea.

206
00:15:51,050 --> 00:15:54,380
Not at all.
I just enjoy tea from time to time.

207
00:15:54,950 --> 00:15:57,980
- By the way,.
- Yes?

208
00:15:58,850 --> 00:16:02,290
It's customary to charge two months' rent upfront.

209
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:04,990
One month rent is impossible to find, anywhere.

210
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:09,190
You're home.
How was school?

211
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:11,090
What's this?

212
00:16:11,970 --> 00:16:13,990
Where are your manners?

213
00:16:16,870 --> 00:16:18,100
- I'm really sorry. Excuse me.
- Sure.

214
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:38,390
What is the matter with you?

215
00:16:38,460 --> 00:16:39,190
Who is he?

216
00:16:39,260 --> 00:16:41,700
He's here to see the room.

217
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:45,600
That guy? Alone?
Are you crazy?

218
00:16:46,170 --> 00:16:48,000
Who are you calling crazy?

219
00:16:48,070 --> 00:16:52,600
Can't you tell?
He's a writer. A gentleman.

220
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:53,800
No way.

221
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:55,840
Why not?

222
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:58,470
Where else will we get money from, huh?

223
00:16:58,550 --> 00:17:00,570
I can't exactly afford to turn him down.

224
00:17:00,650 --> 00:17:02,580
Well, I don't like him.
Send him back.

225
00:17:02,650 --> 00:17:03,880
Send him where?
Keep it down.

226
00:17:03,950 --> 00:17:04,890
I said no.

227
00:17:04,950 --> 00:17:07,080
He'll hear you. Be quiet,
Seong-Ah Hahm!

228
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:07,990
Get him out, now!

229
00:17:08,060 --> 00:17:09,680
He stays.
Settle down!

230
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:10,780
I don't like him.

231
00:17:10,860 --> 00:17:12,190
Be quiet,
Seong-Ah Hahm! Hush!

232
00:17:12,260 --> 00:17:13,290
I don't like him!

233
00:17:15,260 --> 00:17:16,090
I said be quiet!

234
00:17:21,970 --> 00:17:25,600
Oh, you really don't have much stuff.

235
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:29,670
All a writer needs are his laptop and a desk.
What else?

236
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:43,180
You're annoying.

237
00:17:43,260 --> 00:17:45,890
Who rents a room to steal a piece of china?

238
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:50,090
This is the only way to discretely
look for it without the fuss.

239
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:53,690
I can't afford to get in trouble by tying up those girls.

240
00:17:55,670 --> 00:17:57,610
Do you want the table here?

241
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:01,770
Oh, you're here.

242
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:06,870
Shouldn't we sign a lease or something?

243
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,180
Should I ask the realtor?

244
00:18:08,250 --> 00:18:10,680
Oh, no problem.
I don't care if we do.

245
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:14,790
I just don't want to waste any money on brokerage fees.

246
00:18:15,460 --> 00:18:16,980
I'm only here for two months.

247
00:18:18,860 --> 00:18:20,800
Hey, you must be uncomfortable.

248
00:18:20,860 --> 00:18:22,300
I should show you some ID.

249
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:24,590
Oh no.
I didn't mean it like that.

250
00:18:24,670 --> 00:18:26,690
No, no.
We should be clear on this.

251
00:18:28,770 --> 00:18:33,230
My publisher says even authors
need business cards nowadays.

252
00:18:33,310 --> 00:18:34,830
Hyeong-Gook Park,
Author Mangook Publishing

253
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:39,970
- Well, make yourself at home.
- Okay.

254
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:44,980
- See you later.
- Bye.

255
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:22,090
Did you get a tenant?
I saw a man.

256
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:25,590
Yes, I rented out the room upstairs.

257
00:19:25,660 --> 00:19:28,890
A man moved into a house of two girls.

258
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:31,690
He's a writer.
He writes novels.

259
00:19:31,770 --> 00:19:37,300
A man who's a writer moved into a house of two girls.

260
00:19:55,660 --> 00:19:58,680
What's up?

261
00:19:58,760 --> 00:20:01,490
- Um, sir.
- Yes?

262
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:05,400
- I'm really sorry, but...
- Yeah?

263
00:20:06,870 --> 00:20:09,200
- I've been thinking and...
- Well, ma'am,

264
00:20:09,270 --> 00:20:13,300
I paid you two months' rent upfront, right?

265
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:15,470
Yes, two months.

266
00:20:15,540 --> 00:20:18,270
Then I have the right to live here for two months, right?

267
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:19,680
Why, of course...

268
00:20:23,050 --> 00:20:24,490
Did you want to say something?

269
00:20:24,550 --> 00:20:27,580
Um, would you like some dinner?

270
00:20:27,660 --> 00:20:32,290
I only eat fruits when I write.

271
00:20:33,060 --> 00:20:35,690
- How about some tea?
- No thank you.

272
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:38,700
Well, you should get some rest then.

273
00:20:38,770 --> 00:20:39,700
Okay, then.

274
00:20:42,270 --> 00:20:43,200
Good night.

275
00:20:49,150 --> 00:20:50,270
Who's she think she's dealing with?

276
00:21:19,980 --> 00:21:21,100
I love you.

277
00:21:31,850 --> 00:21:32,790
Seong-Ah Hahm!

278
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:46,100
- Oh my...
- He's so hot, isn't he?

279
00:21:46,540 --> 00:21:48,300
Look at you pretending like you don't know.

280
00:21:48,370 --> 00:21:49,900
I really don't know.

281
00:21:49,970 --> 00:21:52,100
- You really don't know?
- I don't.

282
00:21:52,180 --> 00:21:55,670
- You went karaoke-ing that time.
- How would I know that?

283
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:56,770
Then she's all mine.

284
00:22:23,470 --> 00:22:26,810
Let's see who wins this battle.

285
00:22:30,350 --> 00:22:33,580
- You're home early.
- Yeah

286
00:22:34,450 --> 00:22:37,780
It isn't much,
but this is Bolay tea.

287
00:22:37,850 --> 00:22:39,790
I thought you might appreciate gourmet tea.

288
00:22:40,660 --> 00:22:43,490
Oh, thank you.

289
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,390
I haven't tried it yet...

290
00:22:48,660 --> 00:22:51,000
I haven't had that tea, yet.

291
00:22:54,170 --> 00:22:56,100
Oh, would you like some tea?

292
00:22:56,170 --> 00:22:58,700
No, you don't have to.

293
00:22:58,770 --> 00:22:59,710
Thank you.

294
00:23:04,850 --> 00:23:05,870
- Give me a minute.
- Sure.

295
00:23:18,260 --> 00:23:21,290
You have a lot of plants here.

296
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:22,990
Yeah.

297
00:23:23,070 --> 00:23:26,800
It's interesting to put them on the steps like this.

298
00:23:32,780 --> 00:23:36,270
- By the way, sir.
- Yes?

299
00:23:36,350 --> 00:23:38,180
What kind of story are you writing?

300
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:41,570
Well, that's...

301
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:50,890
What I'm writing is...
about a woman.

302
00:23:53,260 --> 00:23:58,700
Once she had many dreams.
She was pretty.

303
00:24:00,070 --> 00:24:02,590
But one day,
she looked back

304
00:24:02,670 --> 00:24:06,400
and those days were gone.

305
00:24:07,180 --> 00:24:11,480
This isn't the life she wanted.

306
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:15,180
She's like my sister,
crying in front of a mirror.

307
00:24:16,950 --> 00:24:18,390
That's what I'm working on.

308
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:23,280
Speaking of,

309
00:24:23,860 --> 00:24:26,790
Could I come down to interview you sometimes?

310
00:24:28,970 --> 00:24:30,190
Me?

311
00:24:30,270 --> 00:24:32,930
Yes.

312
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:37,300
I think you're similar to the character in my novel.

313
00:24:37,370 --> 00:24:41,670
Well, I don't have much of a story.

314
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:43,680
No, no.

315
00:24:44,950 --> 00:24:49,480
Everyone is the main character in their life story.

316
00:24:49,950 --> 00:24:56,880
Oh that.
I put up bricks and plastered with cement.

317
00:24:56,960 --> 00:25:00,590
- Cement?
- Yeah.

318
00:25:03,670 --> 00:25:07,690
You plastered the wall with cement?

319
00:25:07,770 --> 00:25:10,400
Yeah, so it's quiet.

320
00:25:23,250 --> 00:25:26,280
- The whole wall?
- Yes, completely.

321
00:25:28,660 --> 00:25:30,990
- Have a seat, sir.
- Okay.

322
00:25:36,670 --> 00:25:38,690
- Well, sir.
- Yes?

323
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:41,900
I'd hate to bring this up again,

324
00:25:41,970 --> 00:25:43,910
but I asked around and

325
00:25:43,970 --> 00:25:47,100
even a short-term tenant

326
00:25:47,180 --> 00:25:50,370
should pay a deposit.

327
00:25:50,450 --> 00:25:52,380
- Really?
- Yes.

328
00:25:54,050 --> 00:25:56,380
If you can't come up with the deposit right away,

329
00:25:56,450 --> 00:26:00,080
maybe you can pay more rent?

330
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:03,890
Isn't it like 100 dollars more for every 10 grand?

331
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:09,590
Well, you're right.
I will get it to you.

332
00:26:09,670 --> 00:26:11,900
Good.
I will write up the lease.

333
00:26:13,470 --> 00:26:17,000
I thought I told you I don't need the lease.

334
00:26:20,980 --> 00:26:22,470
Hey, Seong-Ah.

335
00:26:22,550 --> 00:26:23,980
Sorry about her.

336
00:26:24,950 --> 00:26:28,180
She's going through puberty.

337
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:28,980
No worries.

338
00:26:33,060 --> 00:26:34,890
Not like it's the first time she's being rude.

339
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:37,690
Where did you learn to behave like this,
in front of an elder?

340
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:39,090
How would that make me look?

341
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:40,590
He's hanging out here now?

342
00:26:40,660 --> 00:26:43,500
Don't overreact.
He's just having tea.

343
00:26:43,570 --> 00:26:45,690
I hate him.
Make him leave.

344
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:48,400
Why are you acting so weird?

345
00:26:48,470 --> 00:26:50,200
He must feel so uncomfortable.

346
00:26:50,270 --> 00:26:52,260
Why are you treating him like he's fecal matter?

347
00:26:52,340 --> 00:26:54,400
How nice,
comparing me to shit.

348
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:57,070
Why can't you be considerate of others?

349
00:26:57,150 --> 00:26:58,770
Whatever. I hate him.
Send him home.

350
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:01,180
How come you hate so many things, huh?

351
00:27:36,950 --> 00:27:39,680
Hey, you're still up studying.

352
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:45,290
I just came out for some air.
I couldn't write.

353
00:27:49,570 --> 00:27:51,090
Alright then.

354
00:27:52,470 --> 00:27:56,000
Here, buy yourself a book.

355
00:28:03,350 --> 00:28:05,470
No discipline around here, huh?

356
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,710
What do you mean,
you can't get through the stairs?

357
00:28:10,090 --> 00:28:12,420
She brick-walled it and plastered cement all over.

358
00:28:12,490 --> 00:28:13,580
And you moved in without even checking that out?

359
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:16,260
Don't get upset.
I'll take care of it.

360
00:28:16,260 --> 00:28:18,690
We assured them it'll only take 3~4 days.

361
00:28:18,760 --> 00:28:21,090
Tell them to wait a few.

362
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:23,100
And send me money for the deposit.

363
00:28:28,370 --> 00:28:32,400
Wow, it's really nice in here.

364
00:28:33,380 --> 00:28:35,670
Did you decorate it yourself?

365
00:28:35,740 --> 00:28:37,680
With my husband.

366
00:28:38,650 --> 00:28:40,480
Here.
What you asked.

367
00:28:41,950 --> 00:28:46,980
By the way,
I need to use the Internet for research,

368
00:28:47,060 --> 00:28:48,890
but I don't get Internet connection from my room.

369
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:52,590
Could I use the computer downstairs?

370
00:28:52,660 --> 00:28:54,690
Well, the computer...

371
00:28:55,260 --> 00:28:56,600
The additional deposit.
Two months worth.

372
00:28:56,670 --> 00:28:58,690
Thank you.

373
00:28:58,770 --> 00:29:02,900
I'll only need to use it for 3~4 days.

374
00:29:03,670 --> 00:29:06,610
That's not going to work.

375
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:07,300
What?

376
00:29:08,340 --> 00:29:11,580
It doesn't look good if you're
downstairs by yourself during the day.

377
00:29:11,650 --> 00:29:16,180
Well, I'll be quiet during the day.
Who's going to see me?

378
00:29:17,450 --> 00:29:21,690
There used to be some unique items
here when the husband was around.

379
00:29:24,060 --> 00:29:26,790
The husband died in a unique fashion last year.

380
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:29,590
Did I say something wrong?

381
00:29:29,670 --> 00:29:32,290
It's okay.
You didn't kill him.

382
00:29:32,370 --> 00:29:36,000
If it's Internet fee,
I will pay you.

383
00:29:36,870 --> 00:29:38,600
I even gave you the deposit.

384
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:42,070
Wait a minute.

385
00:29:42,140 --> 00:29:44,870
I rightfully deserved that deposit.

386
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:47,580
Come on.

387
00:29:48,150 --> 00:29:50,480
Seriously, I only need a month to finish writing,

388
00:29:50,550 --> 00:29:52,680
but I paid rent for two months.

389
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:55,880
Then you asked for more deposit,
which I paid.

390
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:58,890
Still, you won't let me use the Internet?

391
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:01,590
Nowhere in this country can
you rent a room for one month,

392
00:30:01,660 --> 00:30:03,190
not unless it's a motel.

393
00:30:03,270 --> 00:30:05,700
There's a cyber cafe down the street.

394
00:30:05,770 --> 00:30:08,500
How can a writer work in a cyber cafe?

395
00:30:08,570 --> 00:30:11,000
There are loud kids,
playing games.

396
00:30:11,070 --> 00:30:13,100
Why are you yelling at me?

397
00:30:13,180 --> 00:30:15,270
When did I yell?

398
00:30:15,340 --> 00:30:16,680
It's just the Internet.

399
00:30:16,750 --> 00:30:18,470
Just go to the cyber cafe, go!

400
00:30:43,470 --> 00:30:44,600
It's been a while.

401
00:30:45,570 --> 00:30:47,100
You must be out of your prescription.

402
00:30:47,180 --> 00:30:48,580
It must be half-life.

403
00:30:49,550 --> 00:30:52,280
The pills are not working anymore.

404
00:30:52,950 --> 00:30:54,780
You still can't sleep without drinking?

405
00:30:56,850 --> 00:31:00,190
But I don't drink hard liquor.

406
00:31:01,060 --> 00:31:02,990
I only drink wine or beer.

407
00:31:03,060 --> 00:31:04,890
It doesn't matter what kind of alcohol you drink.

408
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:07,900
I told you many times.
Drinking every night isn't good for you.

409
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:10,090
Do you still often get irritated?

410
00:31:10,170 --> 00:31:15,690
But, that's not depression.

411
00:31:15,770 --> 00:31:21,070
Getting angry with people around you,
saying things you regret.

412
00:31:21,140 --> 00:31:23,670
That can also cause you to feel depressed.

413
00:31:25,080 --> 00:31:29,570
Doctor, please.
Stop staring at me like that.

414
00:31:29,650 --> 00:31:30,050
What?

415
00:31:30,120 --> 00:31:32,880
It feels like your eyes are shooting sharp knives at me.

416
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:35,080
I know it's rude of me to say,
but your eyes don't look right.

417
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:37,180
Just when I'm ready to share with you,

418
00:31:37,260 --> 00:31:40,190
I see your eyes and shut up.

419
00:31:40,260 --> 00:31:41,790
I was just walking by and saw,

420
00:31:41,860 --> 00:31:43,890
Jeong-Shim Kim, Psychiatrist

421
00:31:43,970 --> 00:31:45,490
and thought you were a female doctor.

422
00:31:45,570 --> 00:31:47,300
What kind of man has a name Jeong-Shim?

423
00:31:49,270 --> 00:31:50,700
Honestly, if you were a woman,

424
00:31:50,770 --> 00:31:52,400
Maybe I'd feel more comfortable sharing.

425
00:31:52,470 --> 00:31:53,910
But when I'm with you,

426
00:31:53,980 --> 00:31:56,670
I feel like a kid getting scorned by a teacher.

427
00:31:56,750 --> 00:31:58,680
Why can't you make your patient feel at ease?

428
00:31:58,750 --> 00:32:02,080
All you do is criticize and pick me apart.

429
00:32:02,750 --> 00:32:04,580
It's not too late.

430
00:32:05,450 --> 00:32:08,690
Feel free to go else where.
To a female doctor.

431
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:12,280
And my apologies my family named me a girly name.

432
00:32:12,860 --> 00:32:14,390
Do you angry?

433
00:32:17,700 --> 00:32:21,000
Next time,
try this doctor.

434
00:32:21,470 --> 00:32:22,990
She is really feminine.

435
00:32:30,950 --> 00:32:32,280
Got Milk?
Girl Seong-Ah Hahm Today

436
00:32:45,460 --> 00:32:47,290
Did you put shit in your milk?

437
00:32:50,170 --> 00:32:52,500
Mom, the kids are...

438
00:32:55,870 --> 00:32:56,600
Yeah?

439
00:33:01,180 --> 00:33:02,870
Nothing.
Goodnight.

440
00:33:02,950 --> 00:33:03,970
Go to sleep.

441
00:33:18,560 --> 00:33:23,090
What are you doing here?
What if someone sees you?

442
00:33:23,170 --> 00:33:27,400
How is your writing coming along?

443
00:33:27,470 --> 00:33:31,200
How can I write,
when I can't use the Internet?

444
00:33:39,850 --> 00:33:42,980
- Hey, Mister
- Huh?

445
00:33:43,550 --> 00:33:46,580
- Can you buy me a drink?
- What?

446
00:33:46,660 --> 00:33:48,990
What is your name?

447
00:33:50,390 --> 00:33:52,590
Oh, it's Yeon-Joo.
Yeon-Joo Choi.

448
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:59,700
Yeon-Joo Choi...
Yeon as in "become" and Joo as in "jewel"

449
00:33:59,770 --> 00:34:00,790
Joo as in "house"

450
00:34:02,670 --> 00:34:06,000
Joo as in "house" because you own the house.

451
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:08,970
You know, sir.

452
00:34:11,950 --> 00:34:16,480
Do you really think my story can be used for your book?

453
00:34:17,750 --> 00:34:19,080
Sure.

454
00:34:19,150 --> 00:34:23,680
I'm not good at logically telling

455
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:27,490
a story about my circumstances.

456
00:34:27,560 --> 00:34:31,290
No, no, no.
I can totally relate.

457
00:34:32,470 --> 00:34:35,300
I haven't said anything, yet.

458
00:34:37,370 --> 00:34:38,600
Desperation.

459
00:34:39,470 --> 00:34:43,570
Something that desperately asks me to hear you out.

460
00:34:43,650 --> 00:34:46,770
That's hit my imagination.

461
00:34:46,850 --> 00:34:48,080
Hit you?

462
00:34:50,350 --> 00:34:51,280
When did I hit you?

463
00:34:51,350 --> 00:34:55,980
Listen, lady.
You must be my muse.

464
00:34:56,060 --> 00:34:59,590
I will repay you with a great story.

465
00:34:59,660 --> 00:35:01,790
Excuse me.
I have to go to the restroom.

466
00:35:01,960 --> 00:35:02,790
Okay.

467
00:35:16,150 --> 00:35:17,770
How long to copy this?

468
00:35:17,850 --> 00:35:19,080
I'll try to be back by dawn.

469
00:35:19,150 --> 00:35:20,380
That's too late.

470
00:35:20,450 --> 00:35:23,080
Just keep her occupied.
You're good at it.

471
00:35:30,260 --> 00:35:33,290
I got married straight out of high school.

472
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:34,390
No wonder...

473
00:35:35,260 --> 00:35:38,600
I thought it was weird you have a kid in junior high.

474
00:35:41,970 --> 00:35:43,300
Thirty-five.

475
00:35:44,670 --> 00:35:46,900
I'm an oldie in her mid-thirties.

476
00:35:47,940 --> 00:35:49,880
So weird.

477
00:35:49,950 --> 00:35:52,510
Koreans just love it when you say
they look a year or two younger.

478
00:35:52,580 --> 00:35:54,570
If they love looking younger so much,

479
00:35:54,650 --> 00:35:56,580
let's count our age the exact way,

480
00:35:56,650 --> 00:36:00,380
like they do in European Union.

481
00:36:00,460 --> 00:36:03,690
Then you can be in your early thirties.

482
00:36:03,760 --> 00:36:05,390
Early thirties.

483
00:36:05,460 --> 00:36:06,890
Feels different, right?

484
00:36:09,060 --> 00:36:11,000
You're really good with words.

485
00:36:11,070 --> 00:36:13,560
You know, us writers,
we keep a hundred,

486
00:36:13,640 --> 00:36:20,300
no thousands of thoughts in
our heads to get one thing out.

487
00:36:22,410 --> 00:36:24,570
- You're like a con artist.
- What?

488
00:36:25,550 --> 00:36:26,280
Nothing.

489
00:36:30,350 --> 00:36:32,290
Hey, here.
One more.

490
00:36:35,660 --> 00:36:38,790
It goes in,
but keeps getting errors.

491
00:36:39,660 --> 00:36:41,290
I know,
but I'm in a hurry.

492
00:36:42,060 --> 00:36:43,090
What, depression?

493
00:36:43,770 --> 00:36:46,390
At first,
I couldn't figure out what I was feeling.

494
00:36:48,170 --> 00:36:51,610
It was all so sudden,
new emotions. I was going crazy.

495
00:36:51,670 --> 00:36:55,270
I know.
Steel doesn't get rusty overnight.

496
00:36:56,150 --> 00:36:59,880
It takes a lot of time,
being exposed to sun,

497
00:36:59,950 --> 00:37:03,890
and getting rusty by rain.

498
00:37:05,420 --> 00:37:10,590
Sometimes, even washing dishes
seems like an impossible task.

499
00:37:10,660 --> 00:37:13,790
Fatigue.
Simple routine life.

500
00:37:13,860 --> 00:37:19,100
It's easy for homemakers to get depression.

501
00:37:19,170 --> 00:37:20,660
Work out.

502
00:37:20,740 --> 00:37:22,200
Before going to bed,

503
00:37:22,270 --> 00:37:24,100
if you run an hour on the treadmill,

504
00:37:24,170 --> 00:37:26,700
you'll fall asleep like a baby.

505
00:37:27,380 --> 00:37:29,470
I thought this was my interview.

506
00:37:29,550 --> 00:37:32,570
Shouldn't you be listening to me?
Stop interrupting.

507
00:37:34,050 --> 00:37:36,380
I was just trying to help.

508
00:37:36,450 --> 00:37:37,580
Who asked you to help?

509
00:37:40,390 --> 00:37:41,690
Since you're a writer,

510
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:44,590
I thought you'd be a good listener

511
00:37:44,660 --> 00:37:47,290
But I guess not.
All Korean men are the same.

512
00:37:49,770 --> 00:37:52,600
Any old guy can just tell you what to do,

513
00:37:52,670 --> 00:37:56,800
like they have a license to give advice,
issued by government.

514
00:37:58,970 --> 00:38:01,070
What?
You've never seen a woman smoke before?

515
00:38:02,750 --> 00:38:04,080
- Sir!
- Yes

516
00:38:04,150 --> 00:38:06,980
It's my interview.
Let me do the talking.

517
00:38:07,050 --> 00:38:07,780
Okay.

518
00:38:07,850 --> 00:38:09,110
You know, lately

519
00:38:09,180 --> 00:38:11,280
I can't sleep,
at all.

520
00:38:11,890 --> 00:38:14,690
My body is so tired,
but I can't fall asleep.

521
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:17,190
But I can't just get up again.
It wears me out all night.

522
00:38:17,260 --> 00:38:20,920
By the time I close my eyes it's already morning.

523
00:38:22,700 --> 00:38:26,290
Then when I wake up,

524
00:38:26,370 --> 00:38:29,390
I feel depressed all over again.

525
00:38:30,670 --> 00:38:33,900
'I should get out of bed.'
