Come here.

1053
01:28:25,120 --> 01:28:26,250
Let me see.

1054
01:28:37,000 --> 01:28:41,030
I see.
The glasses are great for you.

1055
01:28:42,610 --> 01:28:46,940
They cover up your flaws well.

1056
01:28:48,180 --> 01:28:50,840
I was just trying to hide bags under my eyes.

1057
01:28:51,280 --> 01:28:54,450
You shouldn't be thinking about
killing yourself over nothing.

1058
01:28:58,360 --> 01:29:02,450
There's a Japanese writer,
Murakami Ryu said this once.

1059
01:29:02,530 --> 01:29:04,360
Sex over suicide...

1060
01:29:04,930 --> 01:29:06,660
I'm only in middle school.

1061
01:29:14,310 --> 01:29:15,140
Cheers.

1062
01:29:23,420 --> 01:29:26,940
Confess my love.
Don't confess.

1063
01:29:27,920 --> 01:29:30,650
Confess.
Don't confess...

1064
01:29:47,010 --> 01:29:50,940
Go, Mr. Song.
Go!

1065
01:30:53,610 --> 01:30:54,630
What is it?

1066
01:31:00,410 --> 01:31:01,040
Mom

1067
01:31:01,110 --> 01:31:01,940
Come over here.

1068
01:31:03,020 --> 01:31:04,540
What did he do to you?

1069
01:31:04,620 --> 01:31:05,640
Hey, Yeon-Joo

1070
01:31:07,620 --> 01:31:10,350
What'd you do to my daughter?

1071
01:31:10,420 --> 01:31:12,250
What the...

1072
01:31:19,730 --> 01:31:21,030
Ugh, my back.

1073
01:31:21,100 --> 01:31:23,130
No, Yeon-Joo.
Don't get me wrong.

1074
01:31:23,200 --> 01:31:24,430
What are you doing, mom?

1075
01:31:24,500 --> 01:31:28,240
No, it's not like that.
You got it wrong.

1076
01:31:31,910 --> 01:31:33,140
Open up!

1077
01:31:33,210 --> 01:31:35,540
- You're wrong.
- You're hurting me.

1078
01:31:36,980 --> 01:31:40,650
You're giving me a hard time.
You're wrong.

1079
01:31:42,420 --> 01:31:43,750
Ugh, my back.

1080
01:31:47,130 --> 01:31:49,150
Listen, there's a misunderstanding.

1081
01:31:49,230 --> 01:31:51,060
Let me explain.

1082
01:31:51,130 --> 01:31:53,660
I'm calling the cops.
You can explain it to them.

1083
01:31:53,730 --> 01:31:54,830
Why are you calling the cops?

1084
01:31:55,500 --> 01:31:56,330
Why not?

1085
01:31:56,400 --> 01:31:57,840
- Don't call the cops.
- Why not?

1086
01:31:57,900 --> 01:31:59,130
- Just don't!
- Why?

1087
01:31:59,210 --> 01:32:02,440
Don't, don't.
Just don't!

1088
01:32:05,910 --> 01:32:09,540
Friggin... argh!

1089
01:32:13,350 --> 01:32:15,450
How could you do that to a little girl?

1090
01:32:15,520 --> 01:32:16,550
- Do what?
- It's not like that, mom.

1091
01:32:16,620 --> 01:32:17,450
You just stand back.

1092
01:32:17,520 --> 01:32:20,960
Hey, you're a real piece of work.

1093
01:32:21,030 --> 01:32:23,660
Your kid is having a life or death situation,

1094
01:32:23,730 --> 01:32:26,360
Yet, here you are passed out drunk.

1095
01:32:26,430 --> 01:32:29,730
And what do you do?
Wrongfully accuse me?

1096
01:32:30,600 --> 01:32:33,830
What do you mean she was dying?

1097
01:32:33,910 --> 01:32:38,240
She tried to kill herself.
You daughter, Seong-Hwa. Okay?

1098
01:32:38,310 --> 01:32:40,250
It's not Seong-Hwa.
It's Seong-Ah!

1099
01:32:44,520 --> 01:32:46,450
Why would you want to kill youself?

1100
01:32:46,520 --> 01:32:50,750
What is he talking about?
Tell me he's lying.

1101
01:32:51,420 --> 01:32:53,760
Why do you care if I live or die?

1102
01:32:54,830 --> 01:32:57,160
You already wish I were never born.

1103
01:33:00,130 --> 01:33:02,530
How could you tell her that?

1104
01:33:02,600 --> 01:33:03,830
You did.

1105
01:33:04,240 --> 01:33:06,030
When you got drunk and had a fight with dad!

1106
01:33:06,110 --> 01:33:11,940
Come on, Seong-Ah.
You know I'm not well.

1107
01:33:12,010 --> 01:33:14,950
What are you,
blame it on the depression?

1108
01:33:15,510 --> 01:33:19,640
Do you know why you're depressed?

1109
01:33:19,720 --> 01:33:21,550
It's because your body isn't busy enough.

1110
01:33:21,720 --> 01:33:24,350
Women today don't do anything.

1111
01:33:25,690 --> 01:33:32,060
Your depression could be cured
by working out every morning.

1112
01:33:32,130 --> 01:33:33,160
Don't get smart with me.

1113
01:33:33,230 --> 01:33:35,830
Really, I'm sick of your family.

1114
01:33:36,800 --> 01:33:40,530
Your husband,
Gi-Soo Hahm.

1115
01:33:41,410 --> 01:33:42,740
Didn't he kill himself too?

1116
01:33:43,910 --> 01:33:47,640
He didn't want to live with you.

1117
01:33:47,710 --> 01:33:49,940
So, he fell off the roof.

1118
01:33:50,020 --> 01:33:52,540
Good job,
Gi-Soo Hahm.

1119
01:33:56,290 --> 01:33:57,980
How'd you know?

1120
01:33:58,060 --> 01:33:58,850
What?

1121
01:33:59,630 --> 01:34:02,360
That my husband fell to death.

1122
01:34:03,030 --> 01:34:04,660
You told me.

1123
01:34:05,530 --> 01:34:06,460
No, I didn't.

1124
01:34:08,400 --> 01:34:10,030
How'd you know his name?

1125
01:34:13,110 --> 01:34:14,040
You.

1126
01:34:17,010 --> 01:34:19,030
You killed my husband.

1127
01:34:20,110 --> 01:34:22,050
No, no!

1128
01:34:22,110 --> 01:34:24,340
I didn't do it.

1129
01:34:24,420 --> 01:34:27,050
Come on,
just hear me out. Stay still.

1130
01:34:27,120 --> 01:34:28,640
You're hurting your kid...

1131
01:34:28,720 --> 01:34:29,550
- Go away.
- I will explain everything.

1132
01:34:29,620 --> 01:34:32,060
Stop throwing things.

1133
01:34:32,120 --> 01:34:34,750
Calm down.
I will explain everything.

1134
01:34:34,830 --> 01:34:38,060
Don't!
I am sick!

1135
01:34:38,130 --> 01:34:39,360
What are you doing in my house?

1136
01:34:39,430 --> 01:34:41,130
Stop throwing things.

1137
01:34:41,200 --> 01:34:44,530
Look at me. I'm hurting right now.
Let me explain.

1138
01:34:44,600 --> 01:34:47,130
Why am I here?

1139
01:34:47,210 --> 01:34:48,640
Well, because I am a writer.
I'm here to write.

1140
01:34:48,710 --> 01:34:51,040
You must have a reason for coming here!

1141
01:34:52,910 --> 01:34:54,240
You really want to hear it out?

1142
01:34:55,820 --> 01:34:59,910
Okay, do you know of the Blue Dragon Tea Cup?

1143
01:34:59,990 --> 01:35:01,450
It's a tea cup this small.

1144
01:35:03,620 --> 01:35:04,450
I don't know what you're talking about...

1145
01:35:04,520 --> 01:35:06,050
I think you do.

1146
01:35:06,130 --> 01:35:08,650
Don't Don't!

1147
01:35:08,730 --> 01:35:09,160
- Well...
- Don't.

1148
01:35:09,230 --> 01:35:10,250
Get the hell out of my house.

1149
01:35:10,330 --> 01:35:13,920
Your husband told me.
He hid it in this house somewhere.

1150
01:35:14,000 --> 01:35:15,630
As soon as I get my hands on it,

1151
01:35:15,700 --> 01:35:19,730
I will leave your house,
even if you tell me not to.

1152
01:35:19,810 --> 01:35:22,540
I really don't know anything about it.

1153
01:35:22,610 --> 01:35:25,340
It's 2 million dollars.
Two!

1154
01:35:26,550 --> 01:35:28,040
Mom, let's find it.

1155
01:35:28,110 --> 01:35:30,550
With that money,
the store will be okay.

1156
01:35:30,620 --> 01:35:32,640
The mortgage will be paid for, too.

1157
01:35:32,720 --> 01:35:35,240
And I can afford my cosmetic surgery.

1158
01:35:36,520 --> 01:35:38,750
Nothing to lose, mom.

1159
01:35:45,730 --> 01:35:49,530
Yes, we're keeping on eye on him.

1160
01:36:02,010 --> 01:36:03,040
Over there,
get him!

1161
01:36:11,890 --> 01:36:13,050
Get in,
you idiots!

1162
01:36:27,510 --> 01:36:28,530
Get closer.
Come on!

1163
01:36:33,510 --> 01:36:35,140
Hurry!

1164
01:37:17,720 --> 01:37:18,550
Turn around!

1165
01:38:00,800 --> 01:38:02,130
Hey you!

1166
01:38:13,610 --> 01:38:14,640
You jerk!

1167
01:38:18,720 --> 01:38:20,650
Let go of me!

1168
01:38:21,520 --> 01:38:23,750
Let go of me.
Let go!

1169
01:38:28,130 --> 01:38:29,860
Hey hey!
Get in!

1170
01:38:30,860 --> 01:38:32,960
Come back here, punk!

1171
01:38:38,740 --> 01:38:42,140
So this is the Blue Dragon Tea Cup?

1172
01:38:42,210 --> 01:38:44,940
Can we repair it?

1173
01:38:45,010 --> 01:38:45,740
No, we can't.

1174
01:38:45,810 --> 01:38:49,750
Can we get something similar looking?

1175
01:38:49,820 --> 01:38:51,250
We can't get something like this.

1176
01:38:51,320 --> 01:38:55,050
It will have to be of a certain class
to look like a $10 million piece.

1177
01:38:58,460 --> 01:39:01,860
I believe Mr. Song took the company car out.

1178
01:39:01,930 --> 01:39:02,860
What about it?

1179
01:39:03,330 --> 01:39:07,630
We have dozens of eye witnesses and a security camera.

1180
01:39:08,930 --> 01:39:10,130
Security camera.

1181
01:39:10,970 --> 01:39:13,270
What shall we do now?

1182
01:39:13,340 --> 01:39:15,140
You know I'm frigid.

1183
01:39:15,210 --> 01:39:16,230
Mr. Cho!

1184
01:39:17,410 --> 01:39:19,640
Well, we can report a stolen vehicle

1185
01:39:19,710 --> 01:39:21,740
and make sure Mr. Song doesn't come near the company.

1186
01:39:21,810 --> 01:39:23,340
Can't get too wrong from here.

1187
01:39:23,420 --> 01:39:25,350
Okay, then don't let him near here.

1188
01:39:27,420 --> 01:39:31,550
Then you told me not to let Mr. Song come to work.

1189
01:39:31,620 --> 01:39:33,350
Mr. Song,
Mr. Schmong.

1190
01:39:33,430 --> 01:39:35,760
I need to figure out what to report to my father.

1191
01:39:35,830 --> 01:39:37,460
Can we draw up some paper work?

1192
01:39:37,530 --> 01:39:39,050
You mean,
fix the book?

1193
01:39:39,130 --> 01:39:41,730
Yeah, let's give accounting
100~200 grand and go from there.

1194
01:39:43,100 --> 01:39:45,230
Then, let me fire Mr. Song first,

1195
01:39:45,300 --> 01:39:48,140
and I'll look into accounting.

1196
01:39:50,110 --> 01:39:54,840
Is there really no way to repair this?

1197
01:40:03,120 --> 01:40:06,460
Now, no one will be interested in your house.

1198
01:40:06,530 --> 01:40:09,460
No matter how long it takes,
go through every inch of your place.

1199
01:40:10,900 --> 01:40:14,530
I'm going into hiding for a while.
Call me as soon as you find it.

1200
01:40:16,200 --> 01:40:19,140
Go into hiding, why?

1201
01:40:19,200 --> 01:40:21,930
Do I really have to explain that to you?

1202
01:40:22,010 --> 01:40:23,630
Don't yell at me!

1203
01:40:24,010 --> 01:40:26,140
Walk me through it,
step by step.

1204
01:40:35,620 --> 01:40:37,150
Okay, missus.

1205
01:40:37,220 --> 01:40:40,250
I have to hide out,

1206
01:40:40,330 --> 01:40:42,350
because I am wanted.

1207
01:40:43,230 --> 01:40:45,060
Does that make sense, missus?

1208
01:40:46,030 --> 01:40:48,930
Pull yourself together.
It's 2 million we're talking here.

1209
01:40:49,500 --> 01:40:52,230
Without me,
you can't even sell this.

1210
01:40:52,300 --> 01:40:55,830
Don't let others take it away from you.

1211
01:40:55,910 --> 01:40:57,930
Stay focused!

1212
01:41:01,710 --> 01:41:02,540
I'll be going now.

1213
01:41:10,920 --> 01:41:11,750
Hey

1214
01:41:13,030 --> 01:41:14,250
What about my car?

1215
01:41:14,330 --> 01:41:16,560
Seriously, you're worried about your car?

1216
01:41:18,130 --> 01:41:21,620
You really annoy me,
you know that?

1217
01:41:59,510 --> 01:42:01,340
He was transferred to holdings, yesterday.

1218
01:42:01,410 --> 01:42:04,870
So he wasn't really a writer?

1219
01:42:04,940 --> 01:42:07,640
He was a cultural property smuggler.
With a long list of priors.

1220
01:42:08,980 --> 01:42:11,640
I know I called you out of suspicion,

1221
01:42:12,520 --> 01:42:13,950
But I never thought...

1222
01:42:16,020 --> 01:42:18,460
- What if he...
- Don't you worry.

1223
01:42:18,520 --> 01:42:20,960
He's going to think he got real unlucky and got caught.

1224
01:42:21,030 --> 01:42:23,150
He will never suspect you for turning him in.

1225
01:42:23,230 --> 01:42:25,860
I did some thinking myself.

1226
01:42:27,870 --> 01:42:29,930
Thank you for everything.

1227
01:42:30,000 --> 01:42:32,730
Could I have a cup of coffee?

1228
01:42:32,810 --> 01:42:34,740
We don't drink coffee.

1229
01:42:34,810 --> 01:42:36,140
Oh, Okay.

1230
01:42:44,120 --> 01:42:47,640
Did he say anything else?

1231
01:42:47,720 --> 01:42:49,150
Like what?

1232
01:42:51,020 --> 01:42:53,150
It's nothing.
Never mind.

1233
01:43:00,200 --> 01:43:01,720
You want us to do all of this?

1234
01:43:01,800 --> 01:43:03,530
What are you saying?

1235
01:43:04,000 --> 01:43:07,340
All of these are ours.
Your dads, okay?

1236
01:43:08,210 --> 01:43:09,830
Come on.
Give me a hand.

1237
01:44:45,610 --> 01:44:46,540
It's cold.

1238
01:45:17,940 --> 01:45:18,870
Seong-Ah, don't come out.

1239
01:45:44,400 --> 01:45:46,630
I was a gentleman to you two.

1240
01:45:47,700 --> 01:45:50,930
Out of respect to your husband,
I offered to split it 50:50.

1241
01:45:51,000 --> 01:45:52,030
I'm really sorry.

1242
01:45:52,910 --> 01:45:54,130
By the way,
you must know,

1243
01:45:54,910 --> 01:45:57,140
There are security cameras everywhere.

1244
01:45:58,210 --> 01:45:59,640
You were filmed on your way in,

1245
01:45:59,710 --> 01:46:03,050
down the hallway,
in the elevator.

1246
01:46:03,120 --> 01:46:04,140
Do you think I care?

1247
01:46:04,220 --> 01:46:12,060
Those few minutes on your security
feed isn't going to stop me.

1248
01:46:16,830 --> 01:46:20,530
Nice digs!

1249
01:46:24,300 --> 01:46:25,240
You got here.

1250
01:46:31,410 --> 01:46:32,540
2 million,
my ass.

1251
01:46:33,510 --> 01:46:35,040
I got exactly 200 grand.

1252
01:46:36,020 --> 01:46:38,040
I know you have a million left,

1253
01:46:40,220 --> 01:46:41,740
So don't even think about it.

1254
01:47:07,810 --> 01:47:10,650
What's wrong?
When did this begin?

1255
01:47:13,120 --> 01:47:15,250
I haven't been able to sleep.

1256
01:47:16,720 --> 01:47:20,560
I haven't slept all week.

1257
01:47:22,330 --> 01:47:25,160
I think I'll be fine if I can sleep,

1258
01:47:26,900 --> 01:47:29,530
But I feel awful.

1259
01:47:31,000 --> 01:47:34,730
My life sucks.

1260
01:47:44,920 --> 01:47:48,940
I know how you feel.

1261
01:47:52,930 --> 01:47:55,660
Do you sleep alright now?

1262
01:47:58,530 --> 01:48:00,020
Yes, I sleep just fine.

1263
01:48:03,600 --> 01:48:05,230
I don't even take pills anymore.

1264
01:48:06,610 --> 01:48:10,540
Bitch, you got better alone.

1265
01:48:13,010 --> 01:48:14,640
Can I get a drink?

1266
01:48:15,410 --> 01:48:17,040
I quit drinking.

1267
01:48:19,120 --> 01:48:22,450
Not fair.
Really, not funny.

1268
01:48:24,720 --> 01:48:26,660
I'm doing okay for now,

1269
01:48:28,130 --> 01:48:30,150
But who knows?

1270
01:48:33,700 --> 01:48:36,130
I'm sorry for hitting you earlier.

1271
01:48:38,500 --> 01:48:40,340
We can call it even on the china price.

1272
01:48:41,810 --> 01:48:43,930
What china price are we even on?

1273
01:48:44,810 --> 01:48:47,540
Look at you,
so coy.

1274
01:48:49,010 --> 01:48:50,850
As soon as the bank opens tomorrow morning,

1275
01:48:50,920 --> 01:48:53,040
we're going together to get my money.

1276
01:49:02,530 --> 01:49:04,460
I'm going to lie down here.

1277
01:49:09,200 --> 01:49:12,830
I can't move an inch.

1278
01:49:21,310 --> 01:49:23,540
Are you hungry?
What do you want?

1279
01:49:25,220 --> 01:49:29,350
Your surgery went well, huh?

1280
01:49:30,220 --> 01:49:32,160
Not really.

1281
01:49:32,220 --> 01:49:34,780
It's going to be fine,
once it settles in.

1282
01:49:34,860 --> 01:49:37,160
It's all settled in already.

1283
01:49:41,730 --> 01:49:46,760
Well, the sun will come out again some day.

1284
01:49:46,840 --> 01:49:48,640
It's just life.

1285
01:50:19,410 --> 01:50:22,030
Warm milk will help you fall asleep.

1286
01:50:22,110 --> 01:50:25,840
Damn, I had just fallen asleep.

1287
01:50:36,920 --> 01:50:38,550
Man, it's loud in here.

1288
01:50:46,130 --> 01:50:49,830
So, is he going to move in with us now?

1289
01:50:50,700 --> 01:50:51,230
What?

1290
01:50:51,900 --> 01:50:53,840
You know,
we have to split it in half,

1291
01:50:54,410 --> 01:50:56,240
And we don't have a room to spare.

1292
01:50:57,110 --> 01:51:03,240
Why don't you let me worry about that, alright?
